<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 2:12PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Randolph and central Pocahontas Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 211 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Snowshoe, or 10 miles north of Cass Scenic Railroad,
moving southwest at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mingo and Valley Head.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
